description: Before he was Dominique's faithful soul familiar, Black Benny was a prizefighter and drummer in New Orleans at the start of the 20th century...until an accidental death, a widow's rage and a lonely goddess put him on the wrong side of the death god, Baron Samedi - the side that can get a soul cursed for all eternity.
name: A Bitter Blues for Brother Benny

description: Contains : Uncanny X-Force (2010) #21 , Wolverine and the X-Men (2011) #04-05 , X-Men Legacy (2008) #261,262

Terra Amata has exploded into many little floating islands, and Herbert has become a very dark and very powerful lord, a far cry from his goofy, shoot-from-the-belt self. In both tales in this volume, the key is to find the map to the new world, and a great many forces stand in the way. Whether it's the Dark Lord or even a very upcompromising and very determined Marvin the Red, the new map must be found!
name: The Dark Lord

description: Features an illustrated retelling of one of the most pivitol battles of World War II. Includes historical photos from the WWII, maps, and a who's who run down on the major players. This is a great learning tool and will help anyone, young or old, get caught up on their American History.

volume.name: Fight to the Death: Battle of Guadalcanal

person_credits.name: Bill Watterson
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover
